---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Signature from '@/components/Signature.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="exitcondition" description="Andrew Lee Rubinger's personal blog">
  <main class="px-6 pt-8 pb-8 lg:px-10 flex flex-col">
    <div class="flex gap-8">
      <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <article class="prose">
          <h1>Hi. I'm ALR.</h1>
          <p class="lead text-lg">
            And I think software should meet us where we're at. Simple to share. Yours to improve. And friendlier than a blinking cursor in an empty chatbot.
          </p>
          <div class="not-prose my-10 relative" aria-hidden="true">
            <input
              type="text"
              value=""
              readonly
              tabindex="-1"
              class="w-full rounded-md border border-border bg-card text-foreground text-lg lg:text-xl px-5 py-4 pointer-events-none focus:outline-none select-none caret-transparent"
            />
            <span class="cursor-blink absolute left-5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[2px] h-7 bg-foreground"></span>
          </div>
          <p class="lead mt-0 mb-10 text-lg">
            So I'm building Aileron, a prototype that erases the tech. When it's ready, it'll be a simple place to automate the routines you do every day. On your real systems. 
          </p>
          <p class="lead mt-4 mb-10 text-lg">
            Designed for collaboration. Hardened with privacy and security. Built for real work.
          </p>
          <p class="lead mt-4 mb-10 text-lg">
            Though the work is messy, the result deserves care. These are my thoughts as we fumble through it.


            <Signature />
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
